Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.99,0:01:43.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ahh, how boring...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.91,0:01:47.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't come to Izu beach that often...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.29,0:01:50.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But swimming in this body just isn't fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.71,0:01:54.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I really hope I can return to my real one soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.21,0:01:56.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.51,0:02:01.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.30,0:02:03.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you all right, boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.81,0:02:05.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm fine...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.68,0:02:06.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.98,0:02:09.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.98,0:02:10.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.61,0:02:15.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe I can bear with it for the time being.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.90,0:02:17.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey now, Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.20,0:02:20.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please play seriously!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.49,0:02:23.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan-kun has to be the seeker, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.49,0:02:25.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.04,0:02:27.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, let's start again!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.29,0:02:29.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You have to count to thirty first, all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.50,0:02:34.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.80,0:02:38.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Between those two girls, which did you like the most?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.80,0:02:43.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't hide it, you were taken in by their bodies, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.68,0:02:45.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot, no way.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.39,0:02:51.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it'd be a different story if you were talking about\Nthat girl behind us in the blue striped swimsuit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.31,0:02:53.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.86,0:02:57.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Superimposing that girl's figure\Nwith a certain someone's...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.61,0:03:00.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were having that kind of fantasy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.99,0:03:01.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now look...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.70,0:03:03.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, isn't that Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.99,0:03:06.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.62,0:03:09.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.50,0:03:13.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, why is that little brat here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.38,0:03:14.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dunno.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.38,0:03:18.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, Ran said she was going\Nsomewhere with Sonoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.01,0:03:23.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, the beach the Professor was\Ntalking about was this one?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.60,0:03:25.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.64,0:03:29.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason we didn't bring him was because\Nthere are always cases when he's around!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.39,0:03:33.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all right—it's more fun with more people.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.10,0:03:34.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.57,0:03:47.28,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fs45\pos(309.984,122)}THE MYSTERY IN THE NET
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.57,0:03:47.28,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fs45\pos(308.983,361)}(PART ONE)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.41,0:03:48.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.20,0:03:49.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can run, but you can't hide!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.58,0:03:50.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take this!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.08,0:03:53.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That hurts...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.38,0:03:57.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How's that, ready to give up yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.80,0:04:00.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn, we'll get you next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.51,0:04:02.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko-neesan is so strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.30,0:04:04.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd say more childish than strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.89,0:04:06.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.60,0:04:07.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's Ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.60,0:04:13.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She went back to the shore with Conan-kun\Nwhile you were getting the ball earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.94,0:04:17.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haibara said she was feeling tired, so she went with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.48,0:04:20.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But she said she'll be back soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.20,0:04:30.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her temperature is high, her skin\Nis dry, and she isn't sweating.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.41,0:04:34.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her pupils are contracting and her face is flushed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.87,0:04:37.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, her pulse is quick and strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.38,0:04:40.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She definitely has sunstroke.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.50,0:04:43.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, if that's the case, shouldn't\Nwe take her back to the hotel?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.17,0:04:45.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.68,0:04:49.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As long as she rests in the shade with wet towels\Non her head and chest to cool her down...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.85,0:04:52.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It won't be long before she's feeling better.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.18,0:04:53.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Professor!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.19,0:04:59.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got some water and ice from others on the beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.02,0:05:01.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.15,0:05:03.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, is Ai-chan okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.61,0:05:07.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, her temperature is going\Ndown, so she should be fine soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.12,0:05:09.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm glad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.49,0:05:12.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next time, don't hesitate to tell us\Nif you don't feel well, all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.00,0:05:13.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ai-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.00,0:05:18.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, I'm going to go join the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.71,0:05:19.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.88,0:05:23.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My, Ran-kun really surprised me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.51,0:05:24.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.72,0:05:29.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was the first one to notice\Nsomething was wrong with Haibara.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.89,0:05:32.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's your fault too, Ai-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.31,0:05:36.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you didn't go in the water and just\Nsat there on the shore the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.56,0:05:41.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you were tired, you could have stayed with\Nthe Professor under the beach parasol.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.40,0:05:42.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.49,0:05:46.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doing that have been the same as running away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.45,0:05:50.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Running away? From sharks?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.78,0:05:54.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot, there aren't any sharks on this beach!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.00,0:05:57.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not a shark.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.29,0:06:00.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The opponent was a dolphin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.21,0:06:02.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right—the favorite of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.09,0:06:10.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A malicious shark that's fled from the cold, dark\Nbottom of the sea just cannot compete, can it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.89,0:06:13.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what kind of obscure thing\Nare you talking about now?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.39,0:06:17.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sharks are the more fierce of the two.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.40,0:06:21.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could you go somewhere else?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.44,0:06:22.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm very tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.78,0:06:26.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what are you guys doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.20,0:06:29.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Taking this boat out...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.99,0:06:32.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you were to bump into one of the\Nother visitors, they could be badly hurt!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.91,0:06:34.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's fine, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.08,0:06:39.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was just lying on the beach and the waves\Nare calm, so it'll be fine if we hold it still.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.29,0:06:41.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Sonoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.79,0:06:45.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, we'll take it back immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.09,0:06:47.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.21,0:06:48.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Noboru...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.38,0:06:50.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no need to yell.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.59,0:06:51.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yuuta...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.01,0:06:54.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're scaring the other tourists.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.56,0:06:58.98,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(440.188,349)}Yoshizawa Yuuta (34)\NFisherman
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.89,0:06:58.98,Top,,0,0,0,,This guy just got dumped, so\Nhe's in a bit of a bad mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.81,0:07:04.19,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(320,348)}Shimojou Noboru (34)\NFisherman
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.19,0:07:01.31,Top,,0,0,0,,Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.31,0:07:04.19,Top,,0,0,0,,It was me who dumped that woman!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.69,0:07:07.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, we'll take care of this boat for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.40,0:07:10.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, we were the ones who took it out...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.49,0:07:13.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's quite all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.28,0:07:18.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even cleaning up the trash on the\Nbeach is part of our job as lifeguards.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.50,0:07:21.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lifeguards, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.71,0:07:25.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here I was thinking you were actually\Nfishermen, but I guess I was mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.63,0:07:29.51,Top,,0,0,0,,Well, fishermen who can't get a single fish to bite...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.09,0:07:34.18,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(313.991,349)}Aramaki Giichi (51)\NFisherman
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.51,0:07:34.18,Top,,0,0,0,,Will probably have to clean up the\Nbeach for the rest of their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.39,0:07:36.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wanna say that again?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.18,0:07:38.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the reason we can't catch any fish!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.97,0:07:40.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, calm down, Noboru.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.48,0:07:43.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, Aramaki-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.19,0:07:48.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tonight, at 8:00, we'll be waiting at the\NQueen Hotel's restaurant Tonpu.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.40,0:07:49.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You better not run away!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.28,0:07:52.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course I'll show up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.11,0:07:54.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the ones who better not make a run for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.20,0:07:56.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Ran...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.41,0:07:59.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't the restaurant we made reservations at...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.58,0:08:01.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Chinese restaurant, Tonpu...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.08,0:08:07.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you guys came to have dinner here too?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.50,0:08:10.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, since we're staying at this hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.42,0:08:12.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wanna eat with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.80,0:08:14.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's more than enough room for you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.35,0:08:16.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.89,0:08:17.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's Ai-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.18,0:08:19.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's sleeping in her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.68,0:08:22.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said she wasn't hungry, and would pass on dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.48,0:08:23.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.48,0:08:24.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, what's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.98,0:08:27.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You seem awfully attached to that brown-haired girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.69,0:08:30.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to talk to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.94,0:08:33.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've pretty much never talked...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.40,0:08:35.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when our eyes meet, she averts her gaze.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.78,0:08:38.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe she doesn't like me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.49,0:08:39.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.87,0:08:43.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because Haibara-san said to Conan-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.41,0:08:46.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"She has {\c&HF9EDCD&}good child-bearing hips{\c&HFFFFFF&}, you should be glad."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.41,0:08:46.63,Dialogue,Note,0,0,0,,{\c&HE8E6DC&\pos(257.903,430)}anzan
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.00,0:08:50.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.38,0:08:52.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What were you two talking about!?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.09,0:08:53.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've got it wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.26,0:08:55.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haibara said that on her own!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.30,0:08:57.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.05,0:08:59.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that a good compliment?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.10,0:09:02.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that like {\c&HB6FCE1&}syrup-covered red bean paste and fruit{\c&HFFFFFF&}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.10,0:09:02.60,Dialogue,Note,0,0,0,,{\c&HE8E6DC&\pos(268.92,432)}anmitsu
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.60,0:09:04.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not it at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.14,0:09:06.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It means being able to {\c&HF5BFDE&}calculate by heart{\c&HFFFFFF&}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.14,0:09:06.77,Dialogue,Note,0,0,0,,{\c&HE8E6DC&\pos(429.17,434)}anzan
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.19,0:09:08.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.11,0:09:09.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it wasn't about her butt?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.40,0:09:16.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, did that kid say anything about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.11,0:09:18.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.20,0:09:20.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said that you have a small butt.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.91,0:09:23.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.41,0:09:26.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you happy?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.08,0:09:27.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is small, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.50,0:09:32.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you those brats and girls from this afternoon?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.50,0:09:33.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.01,0:09:37.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, but what time is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.30,0:09:39.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My watch is broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.80,0:09:42.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's 7:12 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.22,0:09:43.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.10,0:09:45.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I came too early.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.60,0:09:52.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, well, looks like a fight is going to\Nbreak out so let's order quick and eat up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.19,0:09:54.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We didn't come here to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.78,0:09:57.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, we do plan to teach that bad guy\Na little something about the rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.49,0:09:59.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rules?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.20,0:10:05.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the inviolable rules of nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.25,0:10:11.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Without regard to where he is, he uses\Na dragnet and takes all the fish?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.59,0:10:17.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we always went with a limited number of\Nfish and allowed the young ones to grow up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.59,0:10:22.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, that guy comes out of nowhere\Nand takes as many fish as he wants.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.39,0:10:27.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why, tonight, we intend\Nto teach that old man a lesson.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.81,0:10:34.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A lesson about how long it'll take to fill the empty\Nocean with fish again due to his transgressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.28,0:10:37.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can't the law punish that person?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.90,0:10:39.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's no use.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.91,0:10:43.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though there's a law against it,\Nit's just empty threats in this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.58,0:10:46.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said he doesn't care, and that\Nhe'll catch as many fish as he wants.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.91,0:10:49.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Yuuta, you're late.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.58,0:10:53.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just now 8:00, you just got here too early.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.59,0:10:54.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.29,0:10:56.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't Nobutsugu come with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.59,0:10:59.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was excited about talking\Nto the old man, wasn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.80,0:11:04.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He called me and said he was going to stop\Nby his dad's grave, so he'd be a bit late.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.18,0:11:06.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.68,0:11:07.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Today's the same day, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.97,0:11:10.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The day that our fathers died.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.02,0:11:12.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your fathers?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.60,0:11:13.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.81,0:11:17.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our dads died on the same fishing vessel...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.90,0:11:20.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was when their ship faced\Na big storm, eight years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.45,0:11:28.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, they say dying at sea is\Nevery fisherman's wish, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.50,0:11:30.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's correct, missy!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.50,0:11:33.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're getting along too well...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.46,0:11:35.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're being rude, Sonoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.50,0:11:36.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.50,0:11:37.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's fine, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.88,0:11:39.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.59,0:11:40.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.80,0:11:45.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true that our dads did still go fishing\Nwhen they knew a storm was coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.39,0:11:45.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.60,0:11:47.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The storm didn't sink the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.18,0:11:54.31,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(324.006,348)}Nezu Nobutsugu (35)\NFisherman
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.60,0:11:51.39,Top,,0,0,0,,That guy sank our fathers' ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.31,0:11:54.31,Top,,0,0,0,,Aramaki's pirate ship did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.81,0:11:57.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, you're telling that story again, Nobutsugu?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.61,0:12:00.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's annoying, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.99,0:12:02.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In any case, where's that pirate?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.49,0:12:04.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He should be here by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.28,0:12:07.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's already 8:40...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.58,0:12:11.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He probably forgot, got drunk, and fell asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.71,0:12:14.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He better not have, or I'll just wake him up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.58,0:12:18.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's useless, we already tried to call him earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.09,0:12:22.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.01,0:12:25.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He picked up?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.68,0:12:29.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He picked up, but isn't saying anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.68,0:12:31.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All I hear is a strange sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.98,0:12:32.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A strange sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.98,0:12:38.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.77,0:12:39.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Waves?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.61,0:12:42.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn, lost the connection.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.19,0:12:43.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That reminds me...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.61,0:12:48.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Aramaki can use the beach as a\Nshortcut to get to this hotel, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.99,0:12:54.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but it's high tide right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.58,0:13:00.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me that old man blew off our\Nmeeting and went fishing instead?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.80,0:13:01.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Couldn't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.88,0:13:04.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, when we sober up a little\Nmore, let's go look for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.18,0:13:06.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, good idea.
Comment: 0,0:13:21.98,0:13:25.49,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(485.258,45)}Detective Conan Episode 246
Comment: 0,0:13:21.98,0:13:25.49,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(498.279,70)}Broadcast August 13, 2001
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.90,0:13:27.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.28,0:13:31.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The three of you were supposed to\Nmeet Aramaki-san tonight at 8:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.41,0:13:36.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The meeting place was the Chinese\Nrestaurant Tonpu at the Queen Hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.37,0:13:40.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, Aramaki-san did not show up on time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.79,0:13:45.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, at around 9:30, you guys decided\Nto come out to check on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.38,0:13:52.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You then found him dead on this\Nbeach with the net all around him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.18,0:13:55.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.69,0:13:59.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please don't make that face at us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.48,0:14:01.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We aren't lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.19,0:14:03.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps not.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.69,0:14:09.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, Aramaki-san and you\Nthree were something like rivals.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.57,0:14:16.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It could be that all of you drowned him, and\Njust said that you found the body together.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.50,0:14:17.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.54,0:14:19.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They really are telling the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.21,0:14:22.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.00,0:14:23.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko-san and Ran-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.71,0:14:30.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We heard them confirm the meeting\Ntime with that guy this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.18,0:14:30.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.18,0:14:36.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, it's true that these people\Nwere at the Chinese restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.73,0:14:37.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hear that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.10,0:14:41.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the three of them came in at different times.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.48,0:14:42.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Agasa-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.40,0:14:46.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That thin guy arrived a little after 7:10!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.11,0:14:49.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This fat guy arrived at exactly 8:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.95,0:14:53.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And this dark-skinned guy arrived around 8:40!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.20,0:14:57.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your children don't look anything like you, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.91,0:15:00.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, they're kids from the neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.58,0:15:05.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Their parents asked me to take them\Nfor a vacation during their school break.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.21,0:15:07.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.51,0:15:10.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan-kun and that strange girl are...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.09,0:15:13.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Ai-kun is back at the hotel, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.55,0:15:16.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan-kun is over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.48,0:15:19.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, hey, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.89,0:15:22.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That won't do, going around and touching things.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.60,0:15:25.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't you think it's strange, Detective Yokomizo?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.78,0:15:27.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.69,0:15:31.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This guy was drowned, but his face\Nand body are covered in scratches.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.40,0:15:34.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not only that, but why does he have a net around him?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.57,0:15:42.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The net was used so that he couldn't move, and he\Nlikely got the scratches while fighting the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.38,0:15:46.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look here, leave that to us police!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.88,0:15:50.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, take the body back for an autopsy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.09,0:15:56.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm, can we go home now?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.60,0:15:59.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have to prepare to go fishing in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.35,0:16:02.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not yet, I still have some questions to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.31,0:16:04.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you suspecting us?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.98,0:16:05.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.90,0:16:09.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were waiting for him at the\Nrestaurant the entire time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.53,0:16:10.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.44,0:16:16.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's possible one of you could have killed\Nhim before going to the restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.49,0:16:19.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And all three of you coming to look\Nfor him at this beach is also...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.70,0:16:21.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exceptionally strange!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.58,0:16:22.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the phone call.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.08,0:16:28.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was already past 8:00, but he hadn't shown\Nup yet so we called him on his cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.00,0:16:32.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't say anything, and hung\Nup right away, but I heard it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.38,0:16:35.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sound of waves through the phone's receiver.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.80,0:16:36.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sound of waves?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.30,0:16:38.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.30,0:16:40.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why we came out here to look for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.31,0:16:45.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This beach is a shortcut from his house to that hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.81,0:16:49.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I called him once while waiting alone over at Tonpu.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.98,0:16:52.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After Yuuta arrived, we tried calling two more times.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.78,0:17:00.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah, I also tried calling him once before\NI got there to make sure he was coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.08,0:17:01.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that really true?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.29,0:17:06.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, even though the call went\Nthrough, he never picked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.50,0:17:11.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you think we're lying, check the\Nincoming calls log on his cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.50,0:17:12.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Yokomizo!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.09,0:17:17.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A cell phone that is thought to have come out\Nof the victim's clothes was tangled in the net.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.80,0:17:18.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What should we do with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.89,0:17:20.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, give it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.01,0:17:22.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Check it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.47,0:17:25.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My number should show up in the log after Yuuta's.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.48,0:17:28.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to this log...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.40,0:17:31.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yoshizawa-san called at 7:02 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.28,0:17:38.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shimojou-san called three times at\N7:47 PM, 8:03 PM, and 8:18 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.74,0:17:42.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Finally, Netsuki-san called once at 8:41 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.70,0:17:47.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, yours was the only call that was answered.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.79,0:17:51.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means that it was either Aramaki-san himself...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.46,0:17:55.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or the one who murdered him that answered the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.09,0:18:00.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why then, did he not answer\NYoshizawa-san and Shimojou-san's calls?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.30,0:18:01.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How would I know?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.01,0:18:04.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Either way, you understand, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.10,0:18:06.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can't be the culprits.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.89,0:18:07.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.60,0:18:13.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the person who answered Aramaki-san's\Nphone was Aramaki-san himself, or the culprit...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.48,0:18:19.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would've been impossible for those\Nthree to have been his murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.49,0:18:23.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it makes no sense for the\Nculprit to answer the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.79,0:18:29.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it was Aramaki-san who answered, why\Ndidn't he answer the four previous calls?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.71,0:18:35.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Aramaki-san was about to be killed, he\Ncould've answered the phone for help...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.09,0:18:38.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's hard to imagine that he'd\Nhang up without saying a word.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.43,0:18:44.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.47,0:18:46.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.68,0:18:49.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The boat we were riding this afternoon?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.48,0:18:50.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It sure is.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.19,0:18:52.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.31,0:18:54.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go get that boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.40,0:18:56.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It may have something to do with this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.48,0:18:56.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.11,0:18:58.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.20,0:19:01.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're thinking about that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.70,0:19:03.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About the day our fathers died.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.58,0:19:09.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, at that time, their boat\Nreturned to this beach in a similar manner, didn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.41,0:19:10.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.54,0:19:16.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the crew missing and a gaping hole in\Nthe side, it was in that horrendous state!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.63,0:19:19.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, those who have died can't be brought back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.67,0:19:21.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let it go, Nobutsugu.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.30,0:19:23.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.76,0:19:24.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.89,0:19:26.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't mess around!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.76,0:19:27.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.47,0:19:30.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Instead of just ordering him around...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.48,0:19:32.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why don't you lend a hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.98,0:19:34.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.56,0:19:37.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That kind of thing is the duty of subordinates...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.15,0:19:41.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be you just don't know how to swim?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.57,0:19:46.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can become a police detective\Nwithout knowing how to swim?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.41,0:19:48.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But your hair looks like coral!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.66,0:19:50.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Coral?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.08,0:19:56.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inside the boat is a 1.8 liter bottle\Nof alcohol and a lone sandal.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.79,0:19:58.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And collected in the bottom of the boat is sea water.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.30,0:20:02.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.51,0:20:05.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why's there a button here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.68,0:20:07.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, the victim's body...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.68,0:20:08.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.81,0:20:13.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim was only wearing one sandal,\Nand one button was missing from his shirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.48,0:20:15.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.90,0:20:20.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit got Aramaki-san\Ndrunk and put him in this boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.40,0:20:24.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, he entangled him in the net before\Ndropping him into the ocean to drown.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.57,0:20:31.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The wounds on his body are from\Nwhen he struggled while in the boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.21,0:20:34.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, isn't this somehow too obvious?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.88,0:20:40.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I were the culprit, I'd just throw\Nthe evidence into the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.80,0:20:41.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.88,0:20:44.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't just throw garbage into the ocean!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.80,0:20:46.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's littering!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.59,0:20:50.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm just saying, if I were the culprit...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.31,0:20:52.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan-kun is the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.27,0:20:54.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't mean that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.31,0:20:56.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I said, "If I were the culprit."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.69,0:20:58.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's a "mininaru"?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.73,0:21:00.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it tasty?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.48,0:21:01.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Agasa-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.15,0:21:05.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I beg you to keep an eye on these children!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.91,0:21:08.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.49,0:21:10.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it all right if we go home now?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.20,0:21:12.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.58,0:21:17.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, why don't you hurry up\Nand check his time of death?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.38,0:21:20.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can't prove our innocence without that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.09,0:21:23.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're working on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.51,0:21:27.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, even though you aren't supposed\Nto throw garbage into the ocean...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.80,0:21:28.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An empty can?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.51,0:21:31.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.31,0:21:36.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.31,0:21:40.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just a little scratch.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.69,0:21:42.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You should be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.61,0:21:45.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are a lot of shells around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.11,0:21:46.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shells?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.57,0:21:50.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Forensics Officer!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.20,0:21:54.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were there any scratches on the victim's cell phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.50,0:21:57.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, lots of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.37,0:21:58.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.08,0:22:00.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.29,0:22:01.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.38,0:22:06.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's hard to imagine that the\Nculprit planned such a coincidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.01,0:22:08.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There has to be something...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.09,0:22:11.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some other purpose!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.27,0:22:23.98,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(303.975,120)}﻿{\fs45}THE MYSTERY IN THE NET
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.27,0:22:23.98,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(310.986,357)}﻿{\fs45}(PART TWO)
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.91,0:22:37.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone's so late.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.55,0:22:47.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.84,0:22:49.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Keep up the good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.34,0:22:49.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.93,0:22:50.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Yokomizo!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.51,0:22:54.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've figured it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.68,0:22:56.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.60,0:22:58.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it you figured out?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.52,0:23:02.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The trick the culprit used to drown that man.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.02,0:23:04.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.99,0:23:10.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with that reaction?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.49,0:23:14.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did the culprit do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.49,0:23:18.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The drifting boat was a fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.41,0:23:21.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The real trick was actually very simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.00,0:23:26.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit got that guy dead drunk...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.21,0:23:29.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then wrapped him in the\Nnet and left him on the beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.88,0:23:36.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The tide will continue to rise but the\Nman, unable to move, will drown.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.43,0:23:39.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, the crime is possible even\Nwithout the culprit being present.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.18,0:23:40.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.81,0:23:42.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko's so smart!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.52,0:23:43.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't I, aren't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.40,0:23:48.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm, sorry to throw cold water\Non you, but that's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.90,0:23:55.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if the tide is rising, that doesn't mean the\Nlevel of water will instantly get that high.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.41,0:24:01.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the waves hitting him, and the water level\Nrising to the point of almost drowning him...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.00,0:24:02.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'd definitely wake up.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.08,0:24:06.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, the victim was only in the net.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.25,0:24:08.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wasn't tied up with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.76,0:24:12.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He could've survived by merely sitting up.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.18,0:24:17.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And still, he would've been able to just crawl to a\Nsafe place where the waves wouldn't reach him.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.18,0:24:23.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That may have worked if he had been given\Nsleeping pills or something along those lines, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.52,0:24:27.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The autopsy report didn't mention\Nanything about drugs in his system.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.73,0:24:29.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, then how about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.19,0:24:35.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit sat on that guy until he drowned!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.82,0:24:36.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.37,0:24:37.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That could work.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.41,0:24:39.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who would call that a trick?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.91,0:24:41.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was so close.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.91,0:24:43.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.71,0:24:45.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.79,0:24:47.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's how it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.50,0:24:52.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why that person said that strange thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.13,0:24:55.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.38,0:24:56.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit is that person!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.47,0:25:00.89,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(320,345)}Shimojou Noboru (34)\NFisherman
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.85,0:24:59.85,Top,,0,0,0,,But that guy still hasn't noticed...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.43,0:25:04.85,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(322.003,340)}Nezu Nobutsugu (35)\NFisherman
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.52,0:25:04.98,Top,,0,0,0,,That the trick he set up to escape from his crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.39,0:25:08.81,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(314.992,345)}Yoshizawa Yuuta (34)\NFisherman
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.60,0:25:08.31,Top,,0,0,0,,Would be the very one that ultimately wrings his neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.82,0:25:14.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, can you hurry up?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.20,0:25:16.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's almost midnight already!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.20,0:25:21.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've already told you everything\Nwe know, so just let us go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.29,0:25:23.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please wait a moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.16,0:25:24.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just a little longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.00,0:25:24.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.50,0:25:27.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We need you to stay here, just a bit longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.54,0:25:29.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Sonoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.42,0:25:32.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't think of any other\Npossibilities for this case, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.09,0:25:34.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go back to the hotel then.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.38,0:25:35.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suppose not.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.22,0:25:39.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.10,0:25:39.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It came?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.51,0:25:42.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The thing that always happens came, didn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.39,0:25:44.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's only a mosquito bite.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.90,0:25:49.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Shinichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.19,0:25:53.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like the investigation won't\Nbe ending soon, so let's go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.11,0:25:55.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stupid, why would we head back now?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.82,0:25:58.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right when the truth behind this\Ncase is about to be revealed...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.66,0:26:00.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By Detective Agasa.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.45,0:26:02.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, does that mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.49,0:26:04.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I understand it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.70,0:26:08.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who drowned Aramaki-san,\Nand the trick the culprit used.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.71,0:26:14.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right now, Mitsuhiko and the others are\Ngathering the materials we'll be needing.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.09,0:26:19.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When they get back, I'll just use your\Nvoice and you follow along as usual...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.80,0:26:22.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.72,0:26:24.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.31,0:26:26.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I left my voice changing bowtie back in the hotel room!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.18,0:26:28.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.19,0:26:30.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.27,0:26:33.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haibara...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.48,0:26:35.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're here, just as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.57,0:26:36.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.49,0:26:39.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how did you know that we were here?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.70,0:26:42.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I waited a long while for you all,\Nand when no one showed up...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.78,0:26:44.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I asked the people at the hotel...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.91,0:26:48.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Is there a murder case being\Ninvestigated around here?"
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.50,0:26:52.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry Ai-kun, I completely forgot about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.08,0:26:55.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, where's everyone else?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.30,0:26:56.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, they're around.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.80,0:26:58.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heeyyyy!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.47,0:27:00.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.89,0:27:02.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We found all of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.51,0:27:04.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here, a big sea shell!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.10,0:27:06.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One dead starfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.39,0:27:08.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.18,0:27:11.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I asked the townspeople for a bucket and a basin.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.19,0:27:14.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what are you going to do with these?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.98,0:27:16.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just wait and see.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.40,0:27:21.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, can't you leave us alone, Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.91,0:27:24.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why won't you just let us go home already?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.28,0:27:30.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because we need to wait until we\Nknow Aramaki-san's time of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.29,0:27:32.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.17,0:27:33.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How long is this going to take?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.96,0:27:37.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The detectives in dramas figure it out in mere seconds!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.71,0:27:42.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, we couldn't have killed him, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.59,0:27:45.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we tried calling him at 8:40...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.89,0:27:49.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The phone was answered but\Nthen was hung up right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.10,0:27:56.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All calls were recorded in the phone log, and all three\Nof us were in the Chinese restaurant the entire time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.98,0:28:01.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're going to suspect us, explain that first!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.70,0:28:07.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How we could've answered the phone while\Nit was with Aramaki's body in the net!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.99,0:28:09.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.70,0:28:11.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because of the waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.79,0:28:14.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.00,0:28:20.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's as if that empty can is Aramaki-san, washed ashore.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.51,0:28:24.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like Aramaki-san, washed ashore...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.80,0:28:27.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.01,0:28:28.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aramaki-san's body rolled over!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.73,0:28:35.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The body was rolled over by the\Npower of waves on the beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.90,0:28:38.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can tell that just by looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.32,0:28:39.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.15,0:28:42.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As Aramaki-san was rolling...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.32,0:28:48.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a chance that the buttons might be\Npressed by a sea shell as the phone rang.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.70,0:28:56.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the body rolled over again, the\Nbuttons got pressed so the call was cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.42,0:29:02.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The proof in this is that the cell\Nphone is covered in scratches.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.72,0:29:07.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not only that, but Aramaki-san\Nhimself was also covered in scratches.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.22,0:29:09.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no doubt about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.60,0:29:15.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The phone being picked up when Nezu-san called\Nwasn't because it was answered by anyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.35,0:29:19.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But only because Aramaki-san's body rolled,\Ncausing the "Call" button to be pushed.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.69,0:29:25.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As such, the culprit was expecting\Nthe body to be rolled over...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.32,0:29:31.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Allowing him to answer and cut the\Ncall without even being there!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.20,0:29:33.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But isn't that just a coincidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.71,0:29:37.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even with the knowledge he would roll over...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.88,0:29:44.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd be impossible to time it so that the body rolled onto\Nsomething and answered the call when you needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.80,0:29:46.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.76,0:29:52.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, with this, your alibis of having been on the\Nphone with him when he died have disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.43,0:29:56.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, tell them to hurry the hell up!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.02,0:29:58.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We need to know the time of death!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.98,0:30:00.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.48,0:30:03.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.28,0:30:05.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The time of death has been determined?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.70,0:30:08.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.20,0:30:09.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.41,0:30:11.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.91,0:30:17.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, stop whispering and tell us already.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.92,0:30:19.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You found out, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.00,0:30:21.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aramaki-san's time of death?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.59,0:30:24.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, we know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.42,0:30:28.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to Aramaki-san's time of death...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.09,0:30:34.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All of you have lost your alibis, and remain suspects!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.68,0:30:36.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.10,0:30:39.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, when are you saying he died?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.60,0:30:42.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How are we supposed to understand if you don't tell us?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.11,0:30:45.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got to the restaurant a little after 7:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.49,0:30:48.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yuuta got there at exactly 8:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.32,0:30:51.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Nobutsugu showed up around 8:40.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.62,0:30:54.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It takes at least ten minutes to\Nget from here to the restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.12,0:31:00.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nobutsugu visited his father's grave before going to the\Nrestaurant, so someone at the temple must've seen him.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.50,0:31:05.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, tell us what time he died!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.50,0:31:09.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we weren't here at the time, we couldn't have...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.55,0:31:11.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't have to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.22,0:31:15.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Being here when it happened isn't necessary...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.39,0:31:19.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you use the following trick!
Comment: 0,0:31:20.81,0:31:24.27,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(487.261,45)}Detective Conan Episode 247
Comment: 0,0:31:20.81,0:31:24.27,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(497.277,71)}Broadcast August 20, 2001
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.94,0:31:27.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Trick?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.90,0:31:31.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Agasa-san, what have you been doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.49,0:31:34.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Getting ready to explain this trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.12,0:31:36.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll soon understand everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.41,0:31:40.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sand in this basin will, naturally, represent the beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.21,0:31:43.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This starfish will represent Aramaki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.09,0:31:48.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the water in this bucket represents the sea water.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.09,0:31:53.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, everyone move away, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.89,0:31:54.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.22,0:32:02.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, dig a hole in the sand big enough for a man to fit in.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.60,0:32:09.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, place the drunk Aramaki-san, who's\Nnow tangled in the fishing net, into the hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.11,0:32:12.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm, Professor Agasa?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.20,0:32:14.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, but that won't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.62,0:32:20.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the trick you're thinking of is immobilizing him\Nwith the net and having the tide kill him...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.91,0:32:21.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It won't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.62,0:32:27.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though the tide is rising, the water\Nlevel doesn't get that high instantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.59,0:32:30.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So if he were about to drown, he'd\Nwake up and would be able to escape...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.71,0:32:32.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to Detective Yokomizo.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.72,0:32:36.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, how about if we use this?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.01,0:32:38.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A sea shell?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.89,0:32:43.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Use it as a weight on top of the victim,\Nand he won't be able to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.52,0:32:46.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.31,0:32:50.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the victim was not only tangled in\Nthe net, but had a weight on him...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.82,0:32:54.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wouldn't be able to get away even if he did wake up.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.11,0:33:00.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's the case, the weight should've still been\Non Aramaki-san when his body was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.00,0:33:03.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, was it there?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.91,0:33:05.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it wasn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.08,0:33:07.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.29,0:33:10.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it were an ordinary weight, it'd still be there, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.80,0:33:14.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the weight had a shape similar to this sea shell...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.59,0:33:18.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is what you'll get.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.10,0:33:21.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It floated!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.68,0:33:24.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, hold on a second...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.39,0:33:27.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of weight has a\Nshape similar to this sea shell?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.52,0:33:29.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be!?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.69,0:33:31.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That boat!?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.61,0:33:33.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.74,0:33:36.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit first got Aramaki-san\Ndrunk and entangled him in the net...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.91,0:33:40.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before digging a hole and putting him inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.70,0:33:44.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, he just had to place a boat on top of the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.91,0:33:51.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, even if the victim did come to, he\Nwould be trapped and would ultimately drown.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.00,0:33:56.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, once the tide came further in, the boat\Nwould merely drift away from the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.51,0:34:00.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All as the person waiting at the\NChinese restaurant wanted...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.80,0:34:02.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shimojou Noburu-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.60,0:34:04.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everything went exactly according to your plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.11,0:34:11.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Noboru...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.69,0:34:13.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me you...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.11,0:34:16.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shimojou-san, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.40,0:34:18.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.99,0:34:20.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.91,0:34:22.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For this next part, just go along with my voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.20,0:34:24.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.45,0:34:30.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about the bottle, sandal, and\Nshirt button found in the boat?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.42,0:34:35.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Their purpose was not only to make you\Nthink Aramaki-san was on the boat...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.09,0:34:38.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But also make you not consider that\Nthe boat was used as a weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.51,0:34:44.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, the sea water in the boat would make it heavier.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.14,0:34:47.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This would make it harder for Aramaki-san to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.43,0:34:52.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true that there's no need to be here\Nto kill the victim with this method, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.82,0:34:55.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why do you think I'm the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.40,0:35:00.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You knew the order of the phone calls in\NAramaki-san's phone log, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.49,0:35:03.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said your call was after Yoshizawa-san's.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.78,0:35:05.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.41,0:35:09.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because he said that he had called before\Nhe came to the Chinese restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.50,0:35:12.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yoshizawa-san arrived at 8:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.58,0:35:15.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You first called at 7:47.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.42,0:35:20.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did you know he called before you did?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.59,0:35:22.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, see, that's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.72,0:35:28.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You knew when Yoshizawa-san\Ncalled Aramaki-san's phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.31,0:35:35.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the phone rang while you were setting\Nup the boat for the trick I just explained.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.90,0:35:36.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.11,0:35:40.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.40,0:35:42.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You just made all of that up.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.99,0:35:47.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't say I'm the culprit just\Nbecause I guessed the order of calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.16,0:35:53.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, you don't even have any evidence\Nthat I used that trick you just went over!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.08,0:35:58.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyone could've gotten him drunk, tangled him\Nin the net, and dropped him into the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.59,0:36:01.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true, Agasa-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.88,0:36:05.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have any evidence proving Shimojou-san did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.30,0:36:07.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There isn't any.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.81,0:36:10.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have no proof that it was you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.02,0:36:14.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I said!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.69,0:36:21.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All you know is that, at that guy's time of\Ndeath, I was at the Chinese restaurant!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.32,0:36:23.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only that truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.49,0:36:25.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have a witness?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.78,0:36:29.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're one of the witnesses!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.33,0:36:32.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really, what time was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.08,0:36:34.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm so forgetful these days...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.79,0:36:36.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.21,0:36:39.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you senile, Gramps?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.59,0:36:41.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was at the restaurant at the table next to yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.80,0:36:43.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right when he died around 8:00!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.22,0:36:47.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please wait a moment, Shimojou-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.39,0:36:50.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.31,0:36:53.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Aramaki-san died around 8:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.81,0:36:57.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I just heard it when you were whispering about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.32,0:37:00.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's rather odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.40,0:37:08.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The time of death reported to me was between\N6:00 and when Aramaki-san was found at 9:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.28,0:37:10.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.70,0:37:12.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You should be able to narrow it down a bit more, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.66,0:37:15.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Using things like rigor mortis and postmortem lividity?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.79,0:37:17.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.46,0:37:20.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Normally the time of death is determined\Nfrom things like postmortem lividity...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.17,0:37:23.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rigor mortis, and rectal temperature, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.76,0:37:28.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's only in cases where the body remains\Nin a fixed place at a fixed temperature.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.60,0:37:33.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In this case, the waves were repeatedly\Nturning Aramaki-san's body over.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.10,0:37:35.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because of that...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.81,0:37:41.86,Dialogue,Sign,0,0,0,,{\pos(303.975,33)}GRAVITY
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.60,0:37:38.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the postmortem lividity is unknown since it's\Ndetermined from the condition of blood
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.90,0:37:41.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that pools at the bottom of the body due to gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.82,0:37:44.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thus, it becomes difficult to hold\Nthe stiffened muscles in place.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.61,0:37:52.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, being constantly hit by the waves caused\Nthe body temperature to change rapidly.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.70,0:37:55.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This makes it hard to determine the time of death\Nfrom the temperature of the body as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.42,0:38:01.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, not even the police know\NAramaki-san's exact time of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.59,0:38:07.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only one who does is the culprit, which is only you!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.86,0:38:20.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Noboru...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.98,0:38:23.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me... it was for our fathers?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.19,0:38:24.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.61,0:38:26.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You should thank me.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.36,0:38:31.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eight years ago, Aramaki killed our fathers while at sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.99,0:38:34.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It took all of my courage to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.00,0:38:36.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eight years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.50,0:38:41.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean the accident that happened when\Nthey sailed into an incoming storm?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.09,0:38:46.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truth is, our fathers didn't\Nwant to challenge that storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.88,0:38:53.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They went out to bring back Aramaki who\Nwent fishing without paying attention to it...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.10,0:38:56.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that bastard...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.43,0:39:01.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He lost control of his own boat due to the\Nwaves and ended up hitting our fathers'!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.69,0:39:07.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, after they had fallen into the ocean,\Nhe just left them all there to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.11,0:39:14.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A sailor who was on the boat with\NAramaki confirmed it for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.70,0:39:15.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, why...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.66,0:39:18.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you take him to the police as a witness?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.50,0:39:21.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He suddenly disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.29,0:39:23.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.00,0:39:28.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I asked Aramaki about him, he just calmly said...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.09,0:39:32.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you want to know how to commit the perfect crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.72,0:39:38.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two people go sailing, and one\Npushes the other into the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.31,0:39:42.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The body's gone and there\Naren't any witnesses around.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.11,0:39:44.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How's that, easy right?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.86,0:39:49.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, Aramaki killed him too?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.82,0:39:54.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even so, you still shouldn't have killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.62,0:39:56.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, you're no different than him.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.62,0:39:59.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hell are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.58,0:40:03.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I took down our enemy for your sake as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.54,0:40:06.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even after I took it upon\Nmyself to be the sacrifice...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.29,0:40:09.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And summoned all my courage to carry\Nout divine punishment on that bastard...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.80,0:40:10.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.76,0:40:13.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could you say that!?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.43,0:40:15.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.47,0:40:17.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.81,0:40:22.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.44,0:40:27.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Courage is a word that gives you\Nthe strength to do what's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.49,0:40:33.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't use it as a reason to take a person's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.29,0:40:48.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran's speech had the murderer at a loss for words.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.92,0:40:52.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In silence, he was taken to the\NShizuoka prefecture police station.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.84,0:40:56.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like a calm that no waves could break...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.60,0:41:01.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Quietly, with a sad smile...
